Assessment:
  Severity: LOW
  Package: cookie (<0.7.0) via @sveltejs/kit
  Impact: cookie name/path/domain out-of-bounds characters
  Applicability to app-startup feature:
    - app-startup domain code (hydrate-feed.ts, hydrate-note.ts, scan-vault.ts,
      parse-markdown-to-blocks.ts, etc.) has NO dependency on the cookie package.
    - The vulnerability is in @sveltejs/kit's HTTP cookie handling, which is
      exercised by the Tauri IPC layer, NOT by the app-startup domain logic.
    - app-startup performs local file system reads via Tauri ports; no HTTP
      request/response handling is in scope.
  Disposition: ACKNOWLEDGED but NOT applicable to app-startup domain scope.
               Infrastructure sprint to update @sveltejs/kit recommended.

